Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.42,0:00:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.42,0:00:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This month we’ll focus on how
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.86,0:00:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we can “serve Jehovah with rejoicing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As parents know, a child is a source
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.66,0:00:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of great joy as well as challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.07,0:00:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how the good example
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,set by these parents\Ninfluenced their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.87,0:00:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think of God’s promised new world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,do images like these come to mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.01,0:00:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sure you’ll enjoy a glimpse
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.05,0:00:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of the future in our new music video.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.29,0:00:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll learn how our joy is enhanced
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.99,0:00:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,when we express appreciation for our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.83,0:00:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for our congregation, and for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.90,0:00:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the February 2020 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.30,0:00:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.89,0:01:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To set the stage, we’d like to begin
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with a few thoughts about the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.66,0:01:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Serve Jehovah With Rejoicing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.70,0:01:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what we are told at Psalm 100:2.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.50,0:01:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you serve Jehovah\Nwith rejoicing all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.27,0:01:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we all will agree
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.28,0:01:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that at times it\Ncan be difficult to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.15,0:01:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, is it really important
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.32,0:01:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve Jehovah with rejoicing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.79,0:01:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does it really mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.09,0:01:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, what is this joyful attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.56,0:01:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah expects from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.93,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And what can we do to serve Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with rejoicing and maintain a joyful spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.94,0:02:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we prove that it is important\Nto serve Jehovah with rejoicing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.97,0:02:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You might think of our goal,\Nwhich is to reflect his personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Timothy 1:11,\Nhe’s called “the happy God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So isn’t it logical that Jehovah expects us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.22,0:02:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happy in his service?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.66,0:02:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In Deuteronomy chapter 28,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we find a report\Nof God’s dealings with the Israelites.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here Jehovah warned them\Nof what would take place
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.17,0:02:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,if they became disobedient
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.37,0:02:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and lost their joy in serving him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.14,0:02:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We read at Deuteronomy chapter 28,\Nbeginning in verse 45:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.38,0:02:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“All these curses\Nwill certainly come upon you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . because you did not listen\Nto the voice of Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“by keeping his commandments and . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“because you did not serve Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:03:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“with rejoicing and joy of heart
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.96,0:03:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when you had\Nsuch an abundance of everything.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah took such good care\Nof the Israelites,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.67,0:03:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet they were not happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This attitude was something\Nhe did not like at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see that serving Jehovah joyfully
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.85,0:03:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This was emphasized by what Jesus taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.99,0:03:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in the Sermon on the Mount,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he helped his audience to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.13,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, this part in Matthew chapter 5
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.47,0:03:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is referred to as the nine happinesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.97,0:03:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, the apostle Paul\Nwrote about “the fruitage of the spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.98,0:03:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy is counted among the aspects\Nof the fruitage of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Being joyful is important,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.72,0:03:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and by means of his spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helps us to rejoice in his service.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.49,0:04:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But is it realistic to expect
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will smile all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and cheerfully sing songs the whole day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, this is not what Jehovah expects.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.67,0:04:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have different personalities\Nand express our happiness differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.68,0:04:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, there are moments in life
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are sad and disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is fully aware\Nthat some of us are not healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.19,0:04:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Others might fight depression
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.89,0:04:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and are therefore at times\Njust not able to express joy in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.86,0:04:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet he loves all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.13,0:04:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and appreciates us very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.60,0:04:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, what is the joy\Nthat Jehovah expects from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is\Nthis joyful spirit, or attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in Deuteronomy,\Nthe term “rejoicing” means
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.39,0:05:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“the inner feeling\Nand the outward manifestation of joy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And we also read about the “joy of heart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.89,0:05:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart stands for\Nwhat we are on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the interior man and is displayed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.43,0:05:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in all his various activities,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,desires, affections, emotions, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,passions, thoughts, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see that joy comes from within us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, does the joy we are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s illustrate: I think it’s safe to say\Nthat we all like sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.60,0:05:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, how does the farmer feel
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.63,0:05:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when he urgently needs it to rain
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s waiting and waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:06:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably would be happier if he had rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.28,0:06:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In these last days, we rarely, if ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have perfect circumstances with no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think we can all agree\Nthat our joy in Jehovah’s service
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is not based on circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.59,0:06:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve had here\Non this program and in our publications
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.70,0:06:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,many examples of ones\Nwho have maintained their joy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s service\Ndespite challenging circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like poor health or opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, what is it\Nthat makes us a happy person?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.02,0:06:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us to open up\Nthe scope of the answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.09,0:06:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would you be willing to join me\Nfor a little experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Please close your eyes for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.69,0:06:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have your eyes closed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.13,0:06:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So now think about an apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.73,0:07:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can open your eyes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think about a red apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a green apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.85,0:07:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or a yellow apple?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you able to answer this question?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All I asked you to do\Nwas to think about an apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.86,0:07:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is, we think in pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we think\Nof countless pictures every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And after we think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like we put\Nall of the pictures in a stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.94,0:07:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we think\Nthe same thought a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like we pull the picture out from below
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.48,0:07:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it on top of the stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.85,0:07:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The longer that we do not think the thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the deeper the picture gets in the stack
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it becomes more difficult to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this stack of pictures\Nrepresenting our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.73,0:08:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is our subconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.80,0:08:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This stack of pictures makes up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.43,0:08:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,our emotional state, or state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It determines whether we are sad or happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.84,0:08:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we are bored\Nor excited, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.15,0:08:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah our Creator\Nis aware of this powerful connection
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.82,0:08:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,between our thoughts  and pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.39,0:08:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s please turn to 2 Kings chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to find one example\Nof how Jehovah made use of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.97,0:08:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we find the report\Nabout the king of Syria
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who wanted to capture Elisha.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.64,0:08:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How did his attendant feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see at 2 Kings chapter 6,\Nbeginning with verse 15:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.65,0:08:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“When the attendant of the man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the true God rose early and went outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.19,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“he saw that an army with horses\Nand war chariots was surrounding the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“At once the attendant said to him:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Alas, my master!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.50,0:09:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we to do?’”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The attendant was in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably thought\Nabout their defenseless position
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.21,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and saw himself\Nalready captured by the Syrian army.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Elisha be able to help his attendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.21,0:09:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 16:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.22,0:09:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“But he [Elisha] said: ‘Do not be afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For there are more who are with us\Nthan those who are with them.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Elisha said:\N‘Think of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.50,0:09:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the many that are with us.’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Did this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the attendant was not able\Nto focus on these reassuring thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He could not envision Jehovah rescuing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah help the attendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.81,0:10:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At 2 Kings 6:17, we read:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.85,0:10:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Elisha began to pray and say:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.59,0:10:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘O Jehovah, open his eyes,\Nplease, that he may see.’
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Immediately Jehovah\Nopened the attendant’s eyes and he saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“and look! the mountainous region
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“was full of horses and war chariots of fire
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.77,0:10:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,all around Elisha.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped the attendant with pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The horses and chariots\Ncaptured his attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,His thoughts now focused on the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah\Nwas with them and in full control.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in his mind,\Nhe already saw Jehovah’s victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.69,0:10:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was not concerned anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.16,0:10:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What he saw influenced his thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and changed his state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.94,0:10:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are so powerful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.44,0:11:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And how considerate Jehovah is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.91,0:11:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, in the end,\NJehovah did not need
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,any of these horses and chariots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.95,0:11:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He saved Elisha and his attendant
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.49,0:11:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,by striking the Syrian army with blindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When we compare the emotions of Elisha
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with his attendant, what made the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances were exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Their thoughts made the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what\Ndoes this have to do with our subject
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.01,0:11:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Serve Jehovah With Rejoicing”?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.41,0:11:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, we have established\Nthat Jehovah expects us to be happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.42,0:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We have seen that our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,can be pictures that influence
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.02,0:11:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who we are and how we feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pictures and thoughts are closely connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why the apostle Paul at Romans 12:2
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,highlights the importance\Nof our thoughts when he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be transformed by making your mind over,”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.84,0:12:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or at Ephesians 4:23,\Nhe emphasizes this by saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.28,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you should continue to be made new
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in your dominant mental attitude.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Both scriptures highlight that our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are critical and have a bearing\Non our whole being.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.43,0:12:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, the apostle Paul knew\Nthat we can change our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.43,0:12:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn with me\Nto 2 Corinthians chapter 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.40,0:12:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what he recommends that we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.17,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here at 2 Corinthians 10:5, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“We are bringing every thought into captivity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it obedient to the Christ.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.58,0:12:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t this exactly what we should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.59,0:12:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We control what we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We avoid occupying our mind\Nwith thoughts that weaken our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.66,0:13:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or thoughts that undermine\Nour determination to serve Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.13,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, we said that thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,are like pictures that stay within us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot delete them,\Nand they will have an effect on how we feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.28,0:13:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But is there something else we can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready for a second experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please close your eyes again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not think of an apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.96,0:13:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can open your eyes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.93,0:13:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you successful\Nin not thinking of an apple?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you probably had to force yourself\Nto think of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.00,0:13:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We are made to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.20,0:13:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the key to serving Jehovah with rejoicing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,lies not just in avoiding negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but also in thinking healthy thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.12,0:13:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians chapter 4 lists a few of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.32,0:14:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We read in verse 8:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.62,0:14:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Finally, brothers, whatever things are true,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.86,0:14:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are of serious concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are righteous,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.77,0:14:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are chaste,\Nwhatever things are lovable,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.30,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are well-spoken-of,\Nwhatever things are virtuous,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.81,0:14:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“and whatever things are praiseworthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.11,0:14:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“continue considering
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[or “thinking about;\Nmeditating on”] these things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.75,0:14:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,By considering and meditating on\Nthese healthy subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we create pictures in our mind\Nthat make it easier for us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.76,0:14:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to display our joy in Jehovah’s service.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Serving Jehovah with rejoicing\Nreally depends on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.97,0:14:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness does not depend\Non our circumstances;
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness comes\Nfrom doing things Jehovah’s way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When we actively control our thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.28,0:14:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we add more pleasant pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.81,0:14:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve experienced things\Nthat make it difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to express happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.02,0:15:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,these unpleasant pictures\Nwill be buried under thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like those listed in Philippians chapter 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.96,0:15:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And gradually
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,our inner peace, contentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and happiness grows\Nand can be seen by others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, our happy God,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.54,0:15:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciates every little step\Nin this direction
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.68,0:15:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s important to him\Nthat we serve him with rejoicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In our first video,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.32,0:15:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll learn another way\Nto serve Jehovah with rejoicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll recall that Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.79,0:15:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is more happiness in giving\Nthan there is in receiving.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And isn’t it true\Nthat when we give commendation, praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and words of appreciation to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.00,0:15:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we experience joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.67,0:15:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following interviews,\Nnotice why some hesitate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.34,0:16:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to express appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.58,0:16:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how they were helped by applying
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.61,0:16:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,lessons they learned from {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I work as a pioneer\Nand also as a commuter at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.37,0:16:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I find this service to be very enjoyable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.27,0:16:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,However, because of my busy schedule,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at times I almost forget\Nto express my appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to the brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.15,0:16:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to express\Nmy appreciation to my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.82,0:16:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but I found myself\Nfeeling bashful in doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew something wasn’t quite natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.93,0:16:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, expressing appreciation\Nis considered to be a virtue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.40,0:17:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But I realized that I needed\Nsome sort of stronger motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Although all ten lepers\Nmust have been grateful,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.04,0:17:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,only one person returned to give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly realized\Nthat even if I feel appreciative,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.42,0:17:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I might fail to express it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.62,0:17:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Esau was an impatient man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.53,0:17:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, David thought deeply
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,about how wonderful pure worship is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to realize\Nthat it is important to think deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.51,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One sister was visiting\Na very sick sister almost every day
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.51,0:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to help her with shopping\Nand was looking after her very tenderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.22,0:17:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As I thought carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.32,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about why she was doing so much\Nand how she felt,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt deep appreciation well up in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.27,0:18:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah richly rewards us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.30,0:18:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah desires\Nto express his appreciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of person am I\Nif I don’t show it from the heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I might be thinking to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that I deserve to be appreciated,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.16,0:18:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,since I am the one providing\Nfor my family, aren’t I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I started thinking\Nabout how Jehovah wants to reward my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.27,0:18:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That made me want to interact with her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.90,0:18:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinder words.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.37,0:18:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that the way I look at her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.41,0:18:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and my facial expressions\Nare changing as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.05,0:18:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets easier\Nto resolve disagreements quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I also feel that we are growing\Ncloser and closer as a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.33,0:19:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,By expressing appreciation,\NI feel very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.73,0:19:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My relationship with brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.30,0:19:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,within the congregation has gotten better,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.63,0:19:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bonds of friendship\Nbetween us are stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.74,0:19:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that the reason why\NJehovah encourages us
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to express our appreciation\Nto others is for our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.11,0:19:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That drew me even closer to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.90,0:19:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Expressing appreciation\Nmay not come easy for some.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.90,0:19:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw,\Nwe may be busy with our spiritual routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.14,0:19:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we are shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.14,0:19:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We may need to make a special effort\Nto get to know our brothers better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But what’s the result if we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We draw closer to them and to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.95,0:20:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that makes us happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.06,0:20:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Being part of a loving family\Ncan bring us great joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It also comes\Nwith responsibilities as parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.13,0:20:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as children, and as siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.94,0:20:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see how three siblings decide
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.81,0:20:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,how to honor their elderly mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.61,0:20:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And please note how vital\Ngood communication in the family is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.13,0:20:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This wasn’t the first health scare with Mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:21:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And my brother and sister
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.24,0:21:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,were always quick to help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.56,0:21:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She’d be here for at least another week\Nand then more long-term care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.42,0:21:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We just weren’t prepared for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have accepted\Nmore help when the friends offered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.87,0:21:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn’t want to be a burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.17,0:22:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Janice understood,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was wondering\Nhow this might affect her Bethel service.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.54,0:22:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrance wished he lived closer\Nso he could do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.52,0:22:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided to pray, sleep on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.39,0:22:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and regroup after doing some research.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.49,0:22:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I shared the example of Joseph in Genesis 45,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.16,0:23:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where he told his father:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.03,0:23:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must dwell in the land of Goshen,\Nwhere you will be near me . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.80,0:23:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I will supply you with food.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.84,0:23:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t let a long distance\Nget in his way of caring for Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.98,0:23:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He took practical steps
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and made his care a priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.80,0:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Janice and Terrance too found great articles
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.63,0:23:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,offering solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.20,0:23:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,such as asking for periodic help,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,making more time to communicate with Mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.30,0:24:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or even getting a part-time nurse.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.24,0:24:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren’t prepared\Nfor her situation to change so suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.41,0:24:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah is guiding us\Nthrough each new challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.43,0:24:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And with his help, we’re honoring Mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.20,0:24:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,making her care our continual priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.34,0:24:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, we saw one way
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.88,0:25:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that a family decided\Nto care for an aging parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.28,0:25:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, situations will differ\Nfrom one family to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.62,0:25:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Each must make a prayerful decision\Nbased on their circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.26,0:25:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you and your family are seeking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.49,0:25:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the right way to honor your elderly parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.23,0:25:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what can help?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.23,0:25:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.30,0:25:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and, as we saw in the video,\Nopen and candid communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.07,0:25:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This, coupled with respect and love,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.94,0:25:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you make a good decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.14,0:25:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we’ll look at the joy and challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.01,0:25:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that come with raising children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.22,0:25:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll travel to Alaska,\Nin the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.15,0:25:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit the Bode family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.55,0:25:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what we can learn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.69,0:25:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,from the example\Nset by the parents, Dale and Nadja.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.00,0:25:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We were serving in a small town in Alberta,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.90,0:25:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we began having children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.40,0:25:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we moved to Craig we had four children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.01,0:26:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And after living here,\Nwe now have nine children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.41,0:26:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You were given this trust,\Nand so as a parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.38,0:26:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to put the Kingdom first;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.69,0:26:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to set a good example;\Nyou need to be at the meetings;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.06,0:26:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to be regular in field service.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.89,0:26:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We really believed\Nthat we needed to love Jehovah first
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.46,0:26:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be\Na good example for our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.97,0:26:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They helped us see that what would make\Nus happy were spiritual things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.24,0:26:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents, more in action than in words,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.24,0:26:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,taught us to seek first the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.08,0:26:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With nine kids,\Nit’s always going to be hectic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.98,0:26:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have extra children;\Nyou have more excuses, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.82,0:26:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Having nine children\Nis a challenge in a million ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.83,0:26:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she had moments where she’d sit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.83,0:26:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in her rocking chair\Nand just look {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}so{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.67,0:27:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one time\Nwhen it was time to go to the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.94,0:27:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was so exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.01,0:27:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought of Isaiah 40,\Nwhere Jehovah says
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.88,0:27:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that “those hoping\Nin Jehovah will regain power.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.78,0:27:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured that Jehovah wants me to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.35,0:27:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to make me\Nstrong enough to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.32,0:27:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I prayed, and I got ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.59,0:27:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a scramble.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In Hebrews, we see the encouragement
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.33,0:27:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to never forsake “our meeting together.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.04,0:27:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad always spoke of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.64,0:27:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a time\Nthat we had to travel in the wintertime,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.74,0:27:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe up to two hours to get to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.65,0:27:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d come back to your home late at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.28,0:27:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, with all these kids\Nthat are worn out—and yourself too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.59,0:27:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing the importance\Nthat they placed on the meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to see\Nthat you never take meetings for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.80,0:28:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents always instilled in us consistency
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.63,0:28:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in field service just like the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.60,0:28:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just what we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.47,0:28:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn’t questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.68,0:28:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We got up on Saturday morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.81,0:28:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got ourselves\Nout the door and in service.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.18,0:28:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn’t simply\Njust be a backseat ornament.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.52,0:28:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew that we were there to give a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.16,0:28:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From an early age,\Nwe were really following the example
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.66,0:28:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of our parents in showing interest in people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.76,0:28:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So because of that,\Nwe enjoyed being in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.03,0:28:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It gave me a sense of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.34,0:28:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I had people to go visit in service.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to know what I was going to talk\Nto them about and have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.78,0:28:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In field service, we would often take breaks
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.01,0:28:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the children and ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.95,0:28:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was important to have our children
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.55,0:29:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy field service—not push them hard
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.96,0:29:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and be too rigid, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.63,0:29:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I think about Proverbs 22:6\Nin the Byington translation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.96,0:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says to “give a boy\Nthe start his course requires.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.00,0:29:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They did that by putting the spiritual things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.57,0:29:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,before the material things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.81,0:29:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped us\Nto be the best parents we could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.58,0:29:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We failed at times, but I always knew\Nthat Jehovah was the best Parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.98,0:29:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we could teach them to love Him,\Nthen he would take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.96,0:29:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we as a family were successful
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.46,0:29:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because we did have Jehovah in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.76,0:29:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All our children
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.76,0:29:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are doing very well in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.10,0:29:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we’re very happy about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.17,0:29:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m sure it makes Jehovah happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.31,0:29:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not have nine children\N—or seven or five or two—
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.04,0:30:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but can’t all parents learn\Na valuable lesson from the Bodes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.85,0:30:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A very important lesson\Nwas mentioned by one of the daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.32,0:30:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,\N“[Our] parents, more in action than in words,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.82,0:30:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,taught us to seek first the Kingdom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.16,0:30:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, despite the many demands\Nof a busy household,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.33,0:30:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dale and Nadja put\Nthe spiritual needs of their family first.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was their example\Nthat had a wonderful influence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.57,0:30:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,on all of their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.51,0:30:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we’ll hear from Brother Stephen Lett\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.55,0:30:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke to the Bethel family\Nabout an enemy of joy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.65,0:30:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and where to find the antidote to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.15,0:30:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my theme is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.15,0:30:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Guard Against Every Sort of Greed.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.66,0:30:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah lovingly gave counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.70,0:30:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jeremiah’s secretary, Baruch,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.70,0:30:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop “seeking great things” for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.70,0:30:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what were those great things?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.70,0:30:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we don’t know for sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.71,0:31:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps prominence\Nor material things or both.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But what bad quality was developing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.45,0:31:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in Baruch’s heart that Jehovah saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.12,0:31:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.12,0:31:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Insight book defines greed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.09,0:31:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as “inordinate or rapacious desire.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.03,0:31:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The dictionary says it’s “a selfish, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.10,0:31:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“excessive desire for more of something
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.87,0:31:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(such as money) than is needed.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.57,0:31:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in effect, Jehovah was telling Baruch,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.11,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Stop being greedy.’
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.47,0:31:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And in an extended application,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.54,0:31:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah tells us the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.05,0:31:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, echoing Jehovah’s counsel to Baruch
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.92,0:31:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is what Jesus tells us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’ll open up to Luke chapter 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.46,0:31:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read our theme scripture here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.62,0:31:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 12:15
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.99,0:31:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—similar counsel from Jesus—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.83,0:31:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 12:15:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.27,0:32:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he [that is Jesus] said to them:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.10,0:32:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Keep your eyes open and guard [now notice]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.47,0:32:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘against every sort of greed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.98,0:32:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘because even\Nwhen a person has an abundance,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.25,0:32:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘his life does not result
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.72,0:32:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from the things he possesses.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.35,0:32:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what makes it a challenge, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.89,0:32:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to “guard against\Nevery sort of greed,” as Jesus counseled?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.76,0:32:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, our three great enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.93,0:32:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, let’s discuss each of these
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.13,0:32:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it makes it a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.13,0:32:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, first, our imperfect flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.20,0:32:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At Genesis 8:21, Jehovah said:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.10,0:32:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“The inclination of the heart of man
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.84,0:32:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is bad from his youth up.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.61,0:32:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And one form of badness is greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.81,0:32:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This tendency toward greed\Nbecomes manifest very early.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.22,0:32:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we see little toddlers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.72,0:32:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,grab things and hold them tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.09,0:32:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mine, mine, mine.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.43,0:33:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That greed is starting to manifest, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.26,0:33:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When people look at a little toddler,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.60,0:33:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they may say,\N“What a cute little boy,”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or “He has his mother’s eyes\Nand his father’s nose.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.74,0:33:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But they never invariably say:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.01,0:33:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look at that little toddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.01,0:33:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What an unselfish little toddler!”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.22,0:33:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it takes a lot of effort\N—doesn’t it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.55,0:33:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach that little one\Nto be unselfish like Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.62,0:33:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what about our\Nsecond great enemy, Satan?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.76,0:33:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Satan’s downfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.96,0:33:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.96,0:33:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He allowed a greedy desire for something 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.40,0:33:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that belonged\Nto Jehovah alone to develop in his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.40,0:33:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was that greed for?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.44,0:33:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.44,0:33:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants his downfall to be our downfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.84,0:33:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to ensnare us in greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.51,0:33:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So he tries to magnify, intensify,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.32,0:33:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,our wrong tendency to be greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.15,0:34:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you think about it, how was Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.36,0:34:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,able to entrap the perfect woman, Eve?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.66,0:34:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He entrapped her in greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.13,0:34:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He got her to crave, desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.03,0:34:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what belonged to God alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.43,0:34:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, he said to her:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.54,0:34:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Eating of all the trees\Nof the garden minus one tree
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.54,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘is not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.61,0:34:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You should crave that one tree
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.98,0:34:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that has not been given to you.’
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.18,0:34:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, let me, please, illustrate
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.62,0:34:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,how greedy Satan made Adam and Eve
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.39,0:34:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—how greedy they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.39,0:34:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like for you to imagine\Nthat you have guests staying in your home,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.89,0:34:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say, “Now, I really want you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.90,0:34:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to make yourselves\Nat home while you’re here.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.17,0:34:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You take them into the kitchen;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.57,0:34:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you open the refrigerator and say:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.57,0:34:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“There are all kinds of food here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.57,0:34:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the cabinets\N—the pantry—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.61,0:34:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“everything you could imagine\Nthat you would want to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.84,0:34:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s yours.\NHelp yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.85,0:34:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t even ask.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.61,0:35:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But then you pull out\None little drawer, and you say:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.85,0:35:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now, I’ve set aside\Nsome items for a later occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.92,0:35:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please, this is very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.92,0:35:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not eat from this one drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.93,0:35:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you’ll find other items just like
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.76,0:35:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“in this drawer\Nin the pantry and the cabinets.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.06,0:35:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll have everything you need.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.07,0:35:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, would that be overly restrictive?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.84,0:35:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Would that be\Nan unloving arrangement with your guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.87,0:35:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d be very generous, wouldn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.01,0:35:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in effect, that’s the arrangement\NJehovah made with Adam and Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.64,0:35:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, back to the illustration:\NIf you came into the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.91,0:35:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and you found your guests eating
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.72,0:35:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that one drawer\Nthat you had not given them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.62,0:35:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you’d be very upset, wouldn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.69,0:35:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’d probably view it as stealing,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.39,0:35:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you likely would put\Nthe thieves out of your house.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.66,0:35:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that illustrates\Nhow Jehovah felt and how Jehovah reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.03,0:35:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But what a protection being content
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:35:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with what was rightfully hers\Nwould have been to Eve!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.07,0:36:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what about\Nour third great enemy—the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.41,0:36:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are relentlessly surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.82,0:36:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by Satan’s world and his spirit,\Ncalled “the spirit of the world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.32,0:36:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say\Nthat Jehovah breathes holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.26,0:36:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to influence his people\Nto act like him and to be unselfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.36,0:36:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But Satan, in effect, exhales
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.13,0:36:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the stinky spirit of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.70,0:36:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes people\Nact like him in being greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.17,0:36:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And one way Satan’s world\Npromotes greed for material things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.61,0:36:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is by relentless advertising.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.78,0:36:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,People are constantly bombarded\Nwith advertisements.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.75,0:36:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, here’s just an example:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.79,0:36:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They may bring out a shiny, new car;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it has about 12 coats of wax on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.69,0:36:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They have all these spotlights shining on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.43,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They bring in a camera\Nfrom all different angles
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and, about this time,\Na scantily clothed woman
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.80,0:37:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,comes strolling out to that automobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.04,0:37:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don’t even notice it, but there’s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.04,0:37:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,soft music playing in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.58,0:37:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As she opens the door and gets in,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.11,0:37:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a crescendo is reached\Nin the background music.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.35,0:37:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re made to feel like,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.69,0:37:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You poor, poor loser
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.06,0:37:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don’t have that car.’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.16,0:37:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t talk about the heavy payments\Nyou’re going to have to make
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.73,0:37:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or how many meetings you’re going to have\Nto miss to make those payments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.63,0:37:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You poor loser if you don’t have that car.’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.60,0:37:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And similar advertising methods\Nare used very often
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.61,0:37:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in promoting\Nmany other gadgets and material things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.95,0:37:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, obviously, we have to fight hard\Nagainst the spirit of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.35,0:37:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we don’t allow it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.45,0:37:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to nurture greed in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.25,0:37:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if we’re not careful,\Nour love for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.62,0:37:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,could be squeezed out
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.63,0:38:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by love for money\Nand love for material things.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.43,0:38:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And if this happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.43,0:38:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than\Nconquering the world as Jesus did,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.70,0:38:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the world will have conquered us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.47,0:38:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it admittedly is a great challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.31,0:38:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to fight these three great enemies and avoid,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.71,0:38:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus counseled, “every sort of greed.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.92,0:38:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, think of that—Jesus indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.19,0:38:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s not just one sort\Nof greed, one kind of greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.56,0:38:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Greed can take on\Nvarious faces, or manifestations,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.03,0:38:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re to guard against all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.03,0:38:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say is the antidote
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.76,0:38:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that can immunize us\Nagainst the poison of greed?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.10,0:38:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is it not contentment?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.30,0:38:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\None sort of greed we talked about,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.21,0:38:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,greed for material things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.21,0:38:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—well, contentment will immunize us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.41,0:38:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,against this terrible form of greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.95,0:39:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re familiar with 1 Timothy 6:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.96,0:39:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“So, having food and clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.96,0:39:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and the footnote adds “shelter.”]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.46,0:39:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we will be content with these things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.40,0:39:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So contentment really protects us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.53,0:39:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in effect,\Nthat’s what Jehovah was telling Baruch;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.04,0:39:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he was telling him:\N‘You have what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.04,0:39:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Stop storing up great things,\Nor seeking great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.91,0:39:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Be content with what you have\Nand do more important things.’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.85,0:39:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he gave a powerful reason\Nwhy Baruch should do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.45,0:39:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told him at Jeremiah 45:5:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.92,0:39:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I am about to bring\Na calamity on all flesh,”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.09,0:39:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so if “you get the mastery over” this,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.66,0:39:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will grant you your life as a spoil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.03,0:39:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the same applies to us, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.44,0:39:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is soon going to bring\Na calamity on all flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.47,0:39:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we need to be content\Nwith what we really need
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.04,0:39:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and ‘seek first the Kingdom.’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.31,0:39:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just ‘temporary residents,’ aren’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.88,0:40:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what 1 Peter 1:17 says.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.45,0:40:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here’s an illustration\Nabout a temporary resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.12,0:40:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like you to imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.12,0:40:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that we rent a venue\Nfor our regional convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.69,0:40:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may do a few things
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.69,0:40:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the stay\Nmore comfortable in that venue.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.60,0:40:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, you may do thorough cleaning;
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.67,0:40:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you might do some touch-up painting;
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.10,0:40:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you might repair\Nsome broken toilets or light fixtures.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.77,0:40:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But you would never paint and plaster\Nthe entire stadium inside and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.68,0:40:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn’t rip up the seats\Nand put all new seating in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.58,0:40:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn’t tear out\Nthe parking lot and put in a new parking lot
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.65,0:40:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know\Nyou’re just a temporary resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.36,0:40:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re going to vacate\Nthat place after the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.02,0:40:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, unlike the illustration, we don’t know\Nexactly when we’re going to vacate,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.43,0:40:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but we know it’s soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.96,0:40:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.47,0:40:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just temporary residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.83,0:40:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Another sort of greed\Nis greed for prominence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.77,0:40:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But being content
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.77,0:41:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with how generous Jehovah\Nhas been in giving us so many privileges
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.44,0:41:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will protect us from this greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.45,0:41:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It would’ve protected Korah in Moses’ time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.95,0:41:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Another sort of greed\Nis greedy sexual desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.52,0:41:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re single or married,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,being content\Nwith what rightfully belongs to us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.33,0:41:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,will really be a protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.63,0:41:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have protected David\Nfrom his sin with Bath-sheba.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.63,0:41:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or there are other sorts of greed,\Nsuch as gluttony and drunkenness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.64,0:41:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But the antidote\Nfor all of these is contentment
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.58,0:41:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—contentment with what is rightfully ours
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.55,0:41:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah has given to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.68,0:41:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we are successful\Nin guarding against every sort of greed,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.99,0:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then we’ll be on hand\Nto enjoy the marvelous time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.52,0:41:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jehovah will open his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.33,0:41:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and satisfy every proper\N“desire of every living thing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.43,0:42:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Full-time service\Nis a special way to serve Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.14,0:42:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with a joyful heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.14,0:42:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens to your joy\Nwhen you suddenly face a serious trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.11,0:42:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jay and Elaine Humer,\Nyou have been through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.48,0:42:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for being here today
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.48,0:42:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to share your personal experience with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.19,0:42:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve enjoyed\Nfull-time service for over 40 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.92,0:42:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,many of those years in the traveling work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.63,0:42:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we’ve had\Nthe wonderful privilege of both pioneering
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.46,0:42:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and serving\Nin the traveling work for 30 years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.76,0:42:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we really feel that Jehovah has been\Nvery kind to allow us to serve him this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.70,0:42:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember\Nwhen I first filled out my application
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.31,0:42:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for regular pioneering back in 1972,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.48,0:42:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought this was my gift\Nto Jehovah—my sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.15,0:42:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the many years
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.15,0:42:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the blessings and the privileges
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.62,0:42:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and how Jehovah helped us\Nthrough some very difficult times,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.12,0:42:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what I thought was my gift to Jehovah\Nturned out to be his gift to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.16,0:42:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very encouraging.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.86,0:43:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you mentioned “difficult times.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.43,0:43:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything\Nin particular you can think of?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.33,0:43:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the hardest things\Nthat we faced was about 20 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.44,0:43:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when we experienced\Nseven deaths in just a six-month period.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.57,0:43:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This really was difficult because five\Nof those seven were family members.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.24,0:43:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jay’s father died,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.25,0:43:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,my aunt Alma (who brought me\Ninto the truth) died, and my father died.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.12,0:43:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So it just seemed\Nlike one layer on top of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.39,0:43:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can hardly imagine how you must have felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.02,0:43:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after such a Job-like experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.43,0:43:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what did you do in order\Nto regain your joy and happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.73,0:43:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it didn’t occur automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.97,0:43:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We kept focused, of course,\Non serving the friends
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.04,0:43:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and working with them,\Nand that kept our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.34,0:43:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from constantly circling around our losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.88,0:43:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We also thought about the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.48,0:43:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We focused on the resurrection hope
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.68,0:43:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and, as we did,\Nit became like “the helmet of salvation,”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.55,0:43:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,protecting our hearts and our thoughts\Nfrom the grief that we were going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.29,0:44:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course,\Nwe shared our hope with others,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.56,0:44:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and that helped us to have it more\Ndeeply engraved on our own hearts as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.19,0:44:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.96,0:44:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, may we learn\Nfrom you what you did in practical terms?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.60,0:44:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The most difficult of all\Nwas about four years after that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.07,0:44:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when our beloved nephew Christopher
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.11,0:44:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was killed\Nin an auto accident at the age of 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.91,0:44:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his parents\Nhad lived with us in the same house
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.31,0:44:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for a number of years\Nbefore we went on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.35,0:44:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we always looked\Nat Christopher like the son
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.58,0:44:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would never\Nhave on this side of Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.99,0:44:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So his death was particularly tragic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.52,0:44:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was excruciating for all of our\Nfamily members, especially his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.03,0:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Christopher was on his way\Nto the Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.00,0:44:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet his papa\Nand his grandmother for field service,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.30,0:44:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and his car hit a patch of ice\Nand slid into an oncoming car.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.27,0:44:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He died instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.27,0:44:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This was so difficult for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.54,0:44:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hearts were broken,\Nand our spirits were nearly crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.65,0:45:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually rendered me speechless,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.88,0:45:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,even to beg for the “groanings\Nunuttered” became very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.02,0:45:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t speak to Jehovah for three days,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.32,0:45:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.99,0:45:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by “listening”?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.03,0:45:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when we were\Nall together as a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.06,0:45:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and my sister just happened to say\Nthat Christopher had been cremated.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.67,0:45:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We were there\Nmaking arrangements for the funeral,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.57,0:45:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just hit me so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.47,0:45:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just—it just hit hard enough
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.54,0:45:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that I fell down, and I just cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.85,0:45:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I laid there on the floor, and I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.68,0:45:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps, maybe Mary\Nfelt this way when she said:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.92,0:45:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Lord, if you’d only been here\Nthis wouldn’t have happened.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.36,0:45:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I laid there,\NI could hear my sister say:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.13,0:45:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go get her Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.63,0:45:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Read her her favorite scripture.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.63,0:45:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Jay did.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.97,0:45:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned to Psalm 91,\Na psalm that I had already memorized,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.50,0:45:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I began to hear Jehovah’s voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.87,0:46:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So was this listening\Nto Jehovah a onetime occurrence?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.88,0:46:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, by no means.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.58,0:46:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I really had to now do my research.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.85,0:46:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I searched\Nfor every article on the resurrection,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.09,0:46:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I searched for every scripture on comfort,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.49,0:46:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I meditated on the artwork\N—the pictures in the publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.19,0:46:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one particular scripture\Nthat really touched my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.40,0:46:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from Psalm 56:8.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.60,0:46:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it said:\N“You keep track of my wandering.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.87,0:46:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do collect my tears in your skin bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.87,0:46:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they not recorded in your book?”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.44,0:46:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought about Jehovah\Ntaking such notice of us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.28,0:46:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—keeping track, watching over,\Neven collecting every tear
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.25,0:46:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and recording each of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.45,0:46:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That truly made me draw close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.92,0:46:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So you continued to listen to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.06,0:46:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by looking at comforting material\Nfrom the publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.80,0:47:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there any\Nspecific article you thought of?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.60,0:47:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an article.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.27,0:47:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about a delicate flower
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.44,0:47:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that had been bent over after a rainstorm
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.77,0:47:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—the kind of cloudburst that would\Nsend humans and animals running for shelter,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.18,0:47:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but not this flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.18,0:47:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it was intact,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.32,0:47:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,bent over but unbroken and still rooted.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.89,0:47:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about us in that same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.42,0:47:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The article said that we can no more\Navoid losing a loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.09,0:47:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,than this flower could\Nuproot itself and run for cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.86,0:47:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.87,0:47:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the article spoke\Na great deal about hope and about faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.44,0:47:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is our anchor, and hope\Nis our preserver of our spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.44,0:47:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And faith\N—James 1:3 stated there that faith—
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.35,0:47:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when it succeeds, we’re able to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.25,0:47:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that’s exactly what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.52,0:47:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It softened the grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.05,0:47:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so like this flower,\Nwe too would stand up and smile one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.29,0:47:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.33,0:48:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the first time I smiled inside,\Nand I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.16,0:48:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh, Jehovah,\Nyou truly are a healer of hearts.’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.70,0:48:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So did you do something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.84,0:48:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I started looking\Nfor some of the artwork in the publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.37,0:48:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And one particular picture\NI found was of a shepherd
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.78,0:48:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,who had gone into\Na bramble bush and rescued a lamb.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.02,0:48:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.35,0:48:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He pulled him out, threw him\Nover his shoulders, and held onto him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.25,0:48:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, ‘What a safe place to be\N—such security!’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.83,0:48:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to take the picture
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.89,0:48:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and to print it out\Nand just enlarge it a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.40,0:48:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I didn’t see\Non the publication page,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.30,0:48:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw when I enlarged it, and there\Nwere scratches on the shepherd’s face.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.31,0:48:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought about what\Nthat shepherd had gone through
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.81,0:48:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to go in the bramble bush and pull him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.38,0:48:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I thought about Jehovah\Nas our Great Shepherd
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lengths that he\Nwent through to rescue us,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.95,0:49:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even at the cost of pain for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.59,0:49:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I was listening and drawing close,\Nback to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.59,0:49:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, what did you do\Nwith these articles and the pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.23,0:49:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I decided to print them all out
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.73,0:49:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—the articles, the pictures,\Nand the scriptures—
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.24,0:49:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I displayed them\Non my desk for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I put them\Nin a big envelope (or like a file),
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.21,0:49:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought that was\NJehovah’s sympathy card to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.05,0:49:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew that we had to do something\Nso as not to be swept away by our grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.39,0:49:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been said that grief is an arduous\Njourney, but one that we cannot avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.82,0:49:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a place where we live\Nbut a passage, as it were.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.39,0:49:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that even though grief\Nnever goes away, it does change over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.50,0:49:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s because Jehovah\Nmade our hearts to heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.43,0:49:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, in time, that’s what we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.44,0:49:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.84,0:49:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not about the lack of faith;\Nit’s simply the price of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.54,0:49:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We loved Christopher, and we miss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.64,0:49:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t like we were leaving him behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.98,0:50:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that’s how you feel\Nwhen you lose a loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.82,0:50:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality, we know\Nthat Christopher is in Jehovah’s memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.22,0:50:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the righteous God,\NJehovah never forgets his loyal ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.56,0:50:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Christopher was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.56,0:50:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re confident\Nthat we’re going to see him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.90,0:50:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what\Nhelps us not to be, as it were,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.10,0:50:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,always looking in the rearview mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.13,0:50:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but looking ahead to the time\Nwhen we will be with him in Paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.34,0:50:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Jehovah truly kept his promises,\Nand he carried us through that storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.34,0:50:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He gathered up the pieces\Nof our broken hearts and sealed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.25,0:50:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though this happened 17 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.55,0:50:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sure, we still have cracks in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.35,0:50:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know for a certainty\Nthat those one day will disappear as well
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.32,0:50:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Paradise\Nwhen we welcome him back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.26,0:50:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, Jehovah\Ntruly proved to be my stronghold,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.96,0:50:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,my Father, and my Friend in a profound way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.77,0:50:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned that Jehovah truly does\Nlove us, cares for us, and protects us.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.77,0:51:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And because he is such a good Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.61,0:51:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,our joy has come back\Nand we have had such a rich life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.95,0:51:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So in all the years that we’ve had\Nthe privilege of serving our God,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.05,0:51:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve always found\Nthat no matter what we give Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.39,0:51:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what sacrifices\Nwe make for him, he always gives us more.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.59,0:51:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot out generous\Nthe most generous Person in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.63,0:51:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, just as he has\Nblessed us all these many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.66,0:51:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we are confident\Nthat he will continue to bless us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.27,0:51:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as we transition to our next assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.40,0:51:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for sharing\Nyour personal experiences with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.74,0:51:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And may Jehovah\Ncontinue to be with the two of you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.68,0:51:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as you now continue\Nyour full-time service as special pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.35,0:51:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And may you be able to apply\Nthe principles that you have just mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.72,0:51:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that Jehovah\Ncan continue to “guard your hearts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.12,0:51:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.66,0:51:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As we discussed earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness does not depend\Non our circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.00,0:52:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but on our thoughts and our outlook.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.00,0:52:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can influence our thoughts\Nby what we picture in our mind’s eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.84,0:52:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that beautifully brought to life
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.67,0:52:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in our new music video entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.38,0:52:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The New World to Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.98,0:52:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a moment now and picture the scene.\NUp ahead on the path are what seem to be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.52,0:52:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Children laughing at play\NIn a world free of the fears we once faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.96,0:52:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And taking care of this beautiful earth\NAre a people that live by our Father’s words:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.97,0:52:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Until the moon is no more”—\NThere is the peace we have been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.18,0:52:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We will feel His love\NUnder the rule of His Son
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.03,0:53:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.04,0:53:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a fire in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.57,0:53:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is an anchor that holds us firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.61,0:53:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a light that shines like the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.75,0:53:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see ourselves there
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.52,0:53:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.03,0:53:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a moment now and think of a place
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.04,0:53:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,By the mountains and rivers or wide open plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.24,0:53:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a place to call home.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.44,0:53:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And now walking in through your front door,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.78,0:54:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There is someone that you know
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.39,0:54:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding out his open arms in hopes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.83,0:54:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of a tearful embrace—
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.26,0:54:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Feels like forever since you’ve been face-to-face.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.97,0:54:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Even death won’t stop
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.51,0:54:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our God’s outstretched love
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.51,0:54:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.36,0:54:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a fire in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.36,0:54:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is an anchor that holds us firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.33,0:54:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a light that shines like the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.47,0:54:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see ourselves there
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.81,0:54:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.85,0:55:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And ev’ry word from His mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.29,0:55:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Will do all for which He sent it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.83,0:55:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s will for this earth is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.36,0:55:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Fulfilling ev’ry living things’ last wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.56,0:55:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a fire in our hearts.\NHope is an anchor that holds us firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.17,0:56:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope is a light that shines like the sun\NAs we see ourselves there
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.08,0:56:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come,\NIn the new world to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.72,0:56:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new world to come,\NIn the new world to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.11,0:56:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll probably want to listen\Nto that song again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.28,0:56:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you might even want to sing it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.85,0:56:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hope is one of the things\Nwe want to focus on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.52,0:56:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And this will have an effect on us;
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.49,0:56:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it will contribute to our being joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.66,0:56:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s conclude\Nthis month’s program with a visit
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.83,0:57:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to a truly beautiful part of the earth:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.10,0:57:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Martinique.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.14,0:57:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This island in the eastern Caribbean
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.64,0:57:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,measures just 50 miles\N(or about 80 kilometers)
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.68,0:57:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by 22 miles (or 35 kilometers).
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.05,0:57:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Martinique,\Nnicknamed the Island of Flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.82,0:57:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,has stunning geographic diversity,\Nwith beaches,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.85,0:57:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,forests, rivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.99,0:57:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sugarcane plantations,\Nand rugged mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.16,0:57:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest point is Mount Pelée,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.50,0:57:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,infamous for causing\Nthe deadliest volcanic eruption
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.63,0:57:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.04,0:57:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When Pelée erupted in 1902,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.17,0:57:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly 30,000 people died\Nbecause they ignored the warnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.04,0:57:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This tragedy is often discussed\Nby our brothers in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.98,0:57:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, more than 4,700 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.88,0:57:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in 62 congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.39,0:57:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,share the good news in eight languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.86,0:57:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,including French, English,\NFrench Sign Language,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.23,0:58:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Arabic, and Creole of Martinique.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.03,0:58:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They conduct more than 4,500 Bible studies
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.53,0:58:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—nearly one per publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.97,0:58:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Over one million tourists\Nvisit this beautiful island every year
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.21,0:58:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,—many by cruise ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.21,0:58:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This presents a unique preaching opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.71,0:58:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The city of Le Marin\Nhosts 55,000 boaters annually.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.42,0:58:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here our brothers preach
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.62,0:58:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“sailboat to sailboat.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.15,0:58:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the city of La Trinité.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.96,0:58:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A Creole of Martinique congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.23,0:58:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was formed here two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.46,0:58:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the congregation has 91 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.77,0:58:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.77,0:58:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They preach\Nin the countryside, the foothills,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.37,0:58:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever people can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.41,0:58:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nin La Trinité, Martinique,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.84,0:58:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,send you\Ntheir warm Christian love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.68,0:58:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.79,0:59:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!
